verbose_text: The patient returned to the hepatitis out-patient department at the beginning of pregnancy with no physical abnormalities, but ALT was elevated to 74 U/l, normal serum alpha-fetoprotein (1.41 ng/ml), positive HBsAg and HBeAg as well as a viral load of 1.7 x 10 8 IU/ml.
